1
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:34,520
=Lady Liberty=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 5=

3
00:01:37,980 --> 00:01:39,980
(Dingqi Reading Platform)

4
00:01:39,980 --> 00:01:40,780
Mr. Fan.

5
00:01:44,700 --> 00:01:45,700
Looking for Gu Yan?

6
00:01:47,180 --> 00:01:48,860
I can only give you
the official response.

7
00:01:49,580 --> 00:01:51,620
I can pass on a message for you.

8
00:01:52,100 --> 00:01:53,700
But as for meeting in person...

9
00:01:55,300 --> 00:01:57,100
Gu Yan isn't taking visitors right now.

10
00:01:57,540 --> 00:01:58,060
Mr. Fan,

11
00:01:58,540 --> 00:02:01,044
authors are supposed to come in
for a weekly briefing.

12
00:02:01,380 --> 00:02:02,300
When is he coming in?

13
00:02:03,060 --> 00:02:04,700
Can't I just get a glimpse of him

14
00:02:04,700 --> 00:02:05,370
from a distance?

15
00:02:05,370 --> 00:02:07,010
He was just here yesterday afternoon.

16
00:02:07,010 --> 00:02:07,740
He won't be back

17
00:02:07,740 --> 00:02:09,660
for another week.

18
00:02:10,900 --> 00:02:11,700
We're setting up

19
00:02:11,700 --> 00:02:12,580
a live chat

20
00:02:12,580 --> 00:02:14,060
between Gu Yan and the readers soon.

21
00:02:14,220 --> 00:02:16,220
I'll let you know
when the stream goes live, okay?

22
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:44,540
That flash drive has

23
00:02:44,540 --> 00:02:46,580
all the archival photos
I found for the author.

24
00:02:46,740 --> 00:02:48,140
It took me a month in the library

25
00:02:48,140 --> 00:02:49,180
to put that together.

26
00:02:49,500 --> 00:02:50,620
If I can't find it,

27
00:02:51,100 --> 00:02:52,300
I'll have to start over again.

28
00:02:52,555 --> 00:02:53,780
Could you check the elevator's

29
00:02:53,780 --> 00:02:55,140
security footage from yesterday?

30
00:02:55,140 --> 00:02:56,500
See if anyone picked it up.

31
00:03:07,820 --> 00:03:09,020
Could you rewind

32
00:03:09,020 --> 00:03:09,888
that part for me?

33
00:03:11,060 --> 00:03:12,100
What about the flash drive?

34
00:03:14,420 --> 00:03:14,940
That guy

35
00:03:14,940 --> 00:03:16,444
looks like an old friend of mine.

36
00:03:16,620 --> 00:03:17,500
Look, Miss.

37
00:03:17,860 --> 00:03:19,300
You're looking for a flash drive.

38
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:22,177
I'm not showing the footage
so you could find your friends.

39
00:03:22,300 --> 00:03:23,260
If you don't see it,

40
00:03:23,260 --> 00:03:24,140
I'm turning this off.

41
00:03:30,580 --> 00:03:31,620
Lin Zhanqiao...

42
00:03:33,660 --> 00:03:35,380
This Gu Yan seems like a rookie.

43
00:03:35,660 --> 00:03:37,980
Probably around twenty-four or five.

44
00:03:38,580 --> 00:03:40,220
He's not among the authors I know.

45
00:03:40,260 --> 00:03:41,500
(Executive Director's Office)

46
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:41,980
Also...

47
00:03:42,820 --> 00:03:43,620
he and Lin Zhanqiao

48
00:03:43,620 --> 00:03:45,466
showed up at Dingqi
around the same time.

49
00:03:48,020 --> 00:03:50,140
If Chenxing doesn't have
a new ace up their sleeve,

50
00:03:51,100 --> 00:03:52,420
why would they let He Han

51
00:03:52,580 --> 00:03:53,420
and Hong Qigong go?

52
00:04:02,740 --> 00:04:03,100
Mantou.

53
00:04:04,220 --> 00:04:05,340
I'm meeting an author today.

54
00:04:05,660 --> 00:04:06,511
I'm leaving early.

55
00:04:06,820 --> 00:04:07,940
What about Hong Qigong?

56
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:09,980
She says she has a high fever

57
00:04:09,980 --> 00:04:10,580
and brain fog.

58
00:04:10,860 --> 00:04:11,620
She's on leave.

59
00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:13,220
Tell her to get plenty of rest.

60
00:04:13,580 --> 00:04:14,450
If she's not worried,

61
00:04:14,450 --> 00:04:15,260
we're not worried.

62
00:04:15,540 --> 00:04:16,140
We don't have

63
00:04:16,140 --> 00:04:17,820
another top-tier author to replace her.

64
00:04:17,820 --> 00:04:18,890
When the rankings come out,

65
00:04:18,980 --> 00:04:20,060
it will look bad for us.

66
00:04:20,220 --> 00:04:21,220
Begging her is worse.

67
00:04:31,780 --> 00:04:32,540
I don't want this.

68
00:04:32,860 --> 00:04:34,300
Krug Champagne is on promotion today.

69
00:04:34,500 --> 00:04:35,511
It's an absolute steal.

70
00:04:35,780 --> 00:04:37,220
Even Yi Shu wrote about it.

71
00:04:37,311 --> 00:04:39,600
She said if she were rich,
she would spend all her money

72
00:04:39,666 --> 00:04:40,755
on Krug Champagne.

73
00:04:40,860 --> 00:04:42,020
It's just that popular.

74
00:04:44,940 --> 00:04:49,700
(Year 2021)

75
00:04:51,260 --> 00:04:54,180
- He Han!
- He Han!

76
00:04:54,460 --> 00:05:04,660
- He Han!
- He Han!

77
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:17,380
Here's to us.

78
00:05:17,380 --> 00:05:18,820
To us!

79
00:05:18,820 --> 00:05:19,820
(Year 2023)

80
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:20,180
Cheers.

81
00:05:20,340 --> 00:05:21,500
Congratulations, Ms. Lin.

82
00:05:21,860 --> 00:05:23,220
Congratulations to you, superstar.

83
00:05:39,300 --> 00:05:40,380
Any other recommendations?

84
00:05:40,700 --> 00:05:41,060
Yes.

85
00:05:41,580 --> 00:05:43,700
We have another champagne here.

86
00:05:44,620 --> 00:05:45,540
But the price

87
00:05:45,540 --> 00:05:46,980
is about the same as the Krug

88
00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:47,860
with today's discount.

89
00:05:48,060 --> 00:05:48,460
Do you...

90
00:05:48,780 --> 00:05:49,980
Thanks for the recommendation.

91
00:05:50,022 --> 00:05:50,860
I'll take this one.

92
00:05:51,060 --> 00:05:51,540
Alright.

93
00:05:51,700 --> 00:05:52,820
I'll bag it for you.

94
00:06:05,540 --> 00:06:05,940
Hello?

95
00:06:05,940 --> 00:06:06,700
Ms. Lin?

96
00:06:06,940 --> 00:06:07,820
I'm your neighbor.

97
00:06:08,220 --> 00:06:09,380
Your mother is at your door.

98
00:06:09,380 --> 00:06:10,420
She passed out from hunger.

99
00:06:11,088 --> 00:06:12,340
I'm on my way. Thank you.

100
00:06:26,020 --> 00:06:26,700
Ms. Lin.

101
00:06:27,060 --> 00:06:28,340
Your mom has been waiting

102
00:06:28,340 --> 00:06:30,220
at your door since this afternoon.

103
00:06:30,860 --> 00:06:32,140
The old lady can't handle that.

104
00:06:32,460 --> 00:06:33,300
I'm fine.

105
00:06:33,380 --> 00:06:34,220
She's busy with work.

106
00:06:34,220 --> 00:06:35,700
It's normal for me to wait.

107
00:06:36,460 --> 00:06:38,180
Next time, I'll just bring some candy

108
00:06:38,180 --> 00:06:39,220
or cookies with me.

109
00:06:39,355 --> 00:06:40,060
Thank you so much.

110
00:06:40,060 --> 00:06:40,660
Are you okay?

111
00:06:40,780 --> 00:06:41,140
I'm fine.

112
00:06:41,266 --> 00:06:41,880
Open the door.

113
00:06:41,980 --> 00:06:42,820
I'm so sorry, Madam.

114
00:06:42,820 --> 00:06:43,844
Thanks for taking care of her.

115
00:06:43,860 --> 00:06:45,220
It was a miscommunication on our part.

116
00:06:45,220 --> 00:06:47,210
You're so busy,
and neglecting your own mother?

117
00:06:47,220 --> 00:06:48,540
Good thing I saw her today.

118
00:06:48,740 --> 00:06:49,620
If I hadn't,

119
00:06:49,780 --> 00:06:51,090
low blood sugar could be fatal.

120
00:06:51,090 --> 00:06:51,980
- It's not that serious.
- You know what I mean.

121
00:06:52,060 --> 00:06:52,700
Thank you.

122
00:06:53,420 --> 00:06:53,820
Thanks.

123
00:06:54,022 --> 00:06:54,540
Come on in.

124
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:58,100
I'm sorry.

125
00:06:58,100 --> 00:06:59,140
I interrupted your work.

126
00:06:59,380 --> 00:07:00,980
You still had things to do, right?

127
00:07:01,500 --> 00:07:03,340
Why don't you go ahead and finish up?

128
00:07:03,980 --> 00:07:04,620
I'll just...

129
00:07:05,180 --> 00:07:06,140
I'll wait for you here.

130
00:07:08,020 --> 00:07:09,540
Didn't I tell you on the phone

131
00:07:09,540 --> 00:07:11,540
that I'd be working really late today?

132
00:07:12,100 --> 00:07:13,340
I told you not to wait for me,

133
00:07:13,340 --> 00:07:14,777
that you could come another day.

134
00:07:15,820 --> 00:07:17,660
I got these vegetables and meat.

135
00:07:17,980 --> 00:07:19,500
It's your father's birthday on Monday,

136
00:07:19,820 --> 00:07:21,940
so I had to get the food ready anyway.

137
00:07:22,700 --> 00:07:24,220
They wouldn't fit in my fridge,

138
00:07:24,540 --> 00:07:26,420
so I brought them over
and put them in yours.

139
00:07:27,066 --> 00:07:29,244
I could make
a couple of dishes for you, too.

140
00:07:29,460 --> 00:07:31,180
So you'd have food after work.

141
00:07:37,820 --> 00:07:38,980
You could've just

142
00:07:38,980 --> 00:07:40,380
bought these groceries on Monday.

143
00:07:40,740 --> 00:07:43,060
You can get this stuff

144
00:07:43,260 --> 00:07:44,740
at the supermarket anytime.

145
00:07:45,260 --> 00:07:45,700
Plus,

146
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:47,330
I barely ever cook at home.

147
00:07:47,330 --> 00:07:49,100
I rarely eat here anyway,

148
00:07:49,580 --> 00:07:50,700
so no need to cook for me.

149
00:07:51,860 --> 00:07:53,260
What if you get hungry at night?

150
00:07:54,100 --> 00:07:56,180
Takeout isn't as healthy
as a home-cooked meal.

151
00:07:57,740 --> 00:07:58,740
Okay, I get it.

152
00:07:58,740 --> 00:07:59,700
I won't do it next time.

153
00:08:00,300 --> 00:08:02,333
Go ahead and do your thing.
Don't worry about me.

154
00:08:02,340 --> 00:08:03,820
I'll leave as soon as I'm done.

155
00:08:05,155 --> 00:08:07,244
Let me put
those flowers in a vase for you.

156
00:08:07,540 --> 00:08:08,380
No, that's okay.

157
00:08:08,700 --> 00:08:09,940
I bought them for a friend.

158
00:08:31,460 --> 00:08:32,140
Hello, Ms. Lin.

159
00:08:32,420 --> 00:08:33,940
I won't be coming to see you today.

160
00:08:34,020 --> 00:08:35,140
Something came up at home.

161
00:08:35,540 --> 00:08:36,660
We'll talk tomorrow.

162
00:08:37,380 --> 00:08:37,940
Also,

163
00:08:38,155 --> 00:08:40,444
send me the updated draft
as soon as it's done.

164
00:08:40,740 --> 00:08:41,860
Okay, got it.

165
00:09:23,220 --> 00:09:24,140
Have you had dinner?

166
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:25,660
I already ate.

167
00:09:25,844 --> 00:09:26,660
Have some fruit, then.

168
00:09:26,820 --> 00:09:27,740
No, I'm good.

169
00:09:32,340 --> 00:09:33,140
(My parents)

170
00:09:33,660 --> 00:09:34,980
(are gentle, kind people.)

171
00:09:36,460 --> 00:09:38,020
(We truly care for)

172
00:09:38,688 --> 00:09:39,660
(and love each other.)

173
00:09:41,088 --> 00:09:42,020
(But we still struggle)

174
00:09:42,020 --> 00:09:43,620
(to find a comfortable level of intimacy)

175
00:09:43,620 --> 00:09:44,460
(that works for us.)

176
00:09:46,380 --> 00:09:48,260
(Do picture-perfect families)

177
00:09:49,620 --> 00:09:50,380
(actually exist?)

178
00:09:52,540 --> 00:09:53,460
(Or are there always)

179
00:09:55,420 --> 00:09:56,500
(hidden flaws?)

180
00:10:15,622 --> 00:10:17,066
(Colorful Culture Media)
Why haven't you left yet?

181
00:10:19,533 --> 00:10:21,450
You were handling matters
outside all by yourself.

182
00:10:21,460 --> 00:10:23,200
It'd be unconscionable
for me to just leave.

183
00:10:25,020 --> 00:10:26,300
Even though you act like a jerk

184
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:27,020
most of the time,

185
00:10:27,420 --> 00:10:28,220
your diligence

186
00:10:28,420 --> 00:10:30,066
is your one redeeming quality at work.

187
00:10:31,180 --> 00:10:32,540
You can talk business with me only.

188
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:34,660
I'm much better at business

189
00:10:34,940 --> 00:10:36,340
than relationships.

190
00:10:36,820 --> 00:10:37,620
That's no fun.

191
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:44,060
I'm starving.

192
00:10:48,260 --> 00:10:49,220
Are you sure Gu Yan

193
00:10:49,340 --> 00:10:50,260
isn't with Dingqi?

194
00:10:51,620 --> 00:10:52,020
Positive.

195
00:10:52,580 --> 00:10:53,780
If he works for Lin Zhanqiao,

196
00:10:54,380 --> 00:10:55,140
we won't be getting

197
00:10:55,977 --> 00:10:57,088
Zhiyuan's money.

198
00:11:00,740 --> 00:11:01,800
You could always go back.

199
00:11:03,340 --> 00:11:04,460
Just tell Lin Zhanqiao

200
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,380
you were blinded by love.

201
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:08,600
But you've calmed down and are ready

202
00:11:09,100 --> 00:11:09,980
to be with her.

203
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:12,066
If you're short on cash, I have some.

204
00:11:13,180 --> 00:11:14,220
We're in the same boat.

205
00:11:16,260 --> 00:11:16,866
Never mind.

206
00:11:17,380 --> 00:11:18,460
I don't work for you.

207
00:11:19,420 --> 00:11:21,020
I want this to be our company.

208
00:11:34,020 --> 00:11:34,860
Only beer today.

209
00:11:36,860 --> 00:11:37,620
But trust me.

210
00:11:38,620 --> 00:11:39,860
Once the company takes off,

211
00:11:40,540 --> 00:11:41,600
and I'm doing better,

212
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:43,700
I'll buy some good wine

213
00:11:45,180 --> 00:11:46,100
and have a nice drink.

214
00:11:50,620 --> 00:11:52,500
I know this sudden romance

215
00:11:52,500 --> 00:11:53,220
isn't for me.

216
00:11:54,060 --> 00:11:54,860
It's for Gu Yan.

217
00:11:57,140 --> 00:11:58,300
But I'm still happy.

218
00:12:00,420 --> 00:12:01,260
At least, you know

219
00:12:01,260 --> 00:12:02,260
I'm useful to you.

220
00:12:03,100 --> 00:12:03,660
That's why

221
00:12:03,660 --> 00:12:05,220
you spend time trying to please me.

222
00:12:06,820 --> 00:12:07,180
Right?

223
00:12:13,580 --> 00:12:14,066
Come on.

224
00:12:32,700 --> 00:12:33,244
Zhao Lanxin.

225
00:12:34,820 --> 00:12:35,380
I'm single.

226
00:12:35,820 --> 00:12:37,140
If you need a fake boyfriend

227
00:12:38,100 --> 00:12:38,900
to start a company,

228
00:12:39,780 --> 00:12:40,980
take photos, post online,

229
00:12:40,980 --> 00:12:42,220
and stroke your ego,

230
00:12:42,340 --> 00:12:42,900
that's fine.

231
00:12:44,300 --> 00:12:45,020
But in private,

232
00:12:45,020 --> 00:12:46,100
drop the act.

233
00:12:47,300 --> 00:12:48,540
I have no interest in dating.

234
00:12:49,780 --> 00:12:51,460
If there's no profit in it,

235
00:12:52,060 --> 00:12:52,900
I won't please anyone.

236
00:12:53,780 --> 00:12:54,420
Not even women.

237
00:12:55,220 --> 00:12:56,820
All relationships are transactional.

238
00:12:57,500 --> 00:12:58,340
On that point,

239
00:12:58,780 --> 00:12:59,700
we agree.

240
00:13:03,540 --> 00:13:04,980
I've got writer's block.

241
00:13:06,220 --> 00:13:07,890
If the female lead gets humiliated

242
00:13:07,890 --> 00:13:09,300
by the salon manager,

243
00:13:09,460 --> 00:13:10,660
what should the male lead do?

244
00:13:11,060 --> 00:13:12,220
The salon is full of women.

245
00:13:12,700 --> 00:13:14,540
He can't just beat someone up

246
00:13:14,540 --> 00:13:16,060
like at the hot pot place.

247
00:13:18,140 --> 00:13:19,620
Just have him buy

248
00:13:19,620 --> 00:13:21,460
the salon.

249
00:13:22,300 --> 00:13:23,140
Fire the manager

250
00:13:23,460 --> 00:13:24,420
and make her the boss.

251
00:13:26,060 --> 00:13:28,020
If she's the boss,

252
00:13:28,220 --> 00:13:30,180
the latter plot
will be too hard for her.

253
00:13:30,740 --> 00:13:32,260
She's too pure and kind.

254
00:13:32,420 --> 00:13:33,820
The staff would also bully her.

255
00:13:34,688 --> 00:13:35,780
Then, have the male lead

256
00:13:35,780 --> 00:13:37,580
interview the staff himself.

257
00:13:37,580 --> 00:13:38,700
Reject the smart ones.

258
00:13:38,700 --> 00:13:40,780
Only keep those purer than her.

259
00:13:42,020 --> 00:13:43,690
It doesn't matter if it runs well.

260
00:13:43,690 --> 00:13:45,060
As long as she's happy.

261
00:13:46,900 --> 00:13:48,740
And she still won't marry him?

262
00:13:49,260 --> 00:13:50,180
Not yet.

263
00:13:50,180 --> 00:13:51,340
She'll agree at the end.

264
00:13:52,340 --> 00:13:53,140
Plus, the male lead

265
00:13:53,140 --> 00:13:54,820
isn't the type to force marriage.

266
00:13:55,220 --> 00:13:56,460
He'll wait until she's ready

267
00:13:56,460 --> 00:13:58,140
and willing before he asks.

268
00:14:10,820 --> 00:14:12,180
Is that what you think too?

269
00:14:12,580 --> 00:14:13,580
Are you waiting

270
00:14:14,220 --> 00:14:15,260
for my "I do"?

271
00:14:15,340 --> 00:14:16,820
I'm not.

272
00:14:17,100 --> 00:14:17,940
Definitely not.

273
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:19,460
I am the type

274
00:14:19,460 --> 00:14:20,820
to force marriage.

275
00:14:21,060 --> 00:14:22,020
So if I haven't asked,

276
00:14:22,020 --> 00:14:23,300
I haven't thought about it.

277
00:14:25,620 --> 00:14:27,260
Go update your chapter.

278
00:14:27,780 --> 00:14:28,140
Be good.

279
00:14:29,220 --> 00:14:30,020
So you're staying up

280
00:14:30,020 --> 00:14:31,140
to wait for my update?

281
00:14:31,300 --> 00:14:32,860
Yes, that's the case.

282
00:14:33,660 --> 00:14:34,340
I'll get to it.

283
00:14:34,980 --> 00:14:35,700
Wait for me.

284
00:14:42,060 --> 00:14:43,740
(Gu Yan's "Drunk Old Friend" updated.)

285
00:14:43,940 --> 00:14:44,740
(Drunk Old Friend)

286
00:14:44,740 --> 00:14:45,460
(Start Reading)

287
00:14:48,340 --> 00:14:53,700
(Chapter 63: The Dance Mystery III)

288
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:56,900
Don't fall asleep.

289
00:14:56,900 --> 00:14:57,900
I'm updating soon.

290
00:14:58,020 --> 00:14:58,980
Another 20 minutes.

291
00:14:59,220 --> 00:14:59,940
It'll be ready.

292
00:15:06,660 --> 00:15:09,020
(Select Tip Amount)

293
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:36,860
I'm leaving.

294
00:15:36,860 --> 00:15:38,100
Take care of yourself.

295
00:15:38,540 --> 00:15:40,180
Don't work too hard.

296
00:15:40,660 --> 00:15:41,820
There's food in the fridge.

297
00:15:41,820 --> 00:15:44,100
Bring it to your dad soon.

298
00:16:18,780 --> 00:16:20,860
(For Lin)

299
00:16:20,860 --> 00:16:24,700
(For Monday morning,
expiring Tuesday afternoon.)

300
00:16:25,420 --> 00:16:26,540
Tomorrow at 10:30 AM,

301
00:16:26,620 --> 00:16:27,780
Gu Yan will have a livestream

302
00:16:27,780 --> 00:16:28,850
on Dingqi Reading Platform.

303
00:16:28,860 --> 00:16:29,540
I'll go early

304
00:16:29,620 --> 00:16:30,660
to try to chat with him.

305
00:16:30,860 --> 00:16:32,060
You won't get a chance there.

306
00:16:33,060 --> 00:16:34,620
Better to print out our terms

307
00:16:34,620 --> 00:16:35,780
and offers for him

308
00:16:36,020 --> 00:16:36,780
to read.

309
00:16:37,180 --> 00:16:37,980
They're all ready.

310
00:16:40,220 --> 00:16:41,970
So our priorities are...

311
00:16:41,970 --> 00:16:43,220
First, Gu Yan.

312
00:16:43,580 --> 00:16:44,460
Second, Hong Qigong.

313
00:16:45,180 --> 00:16:46,740
Third, Zhugan Dalang.

314
00:16:46,980 --> 00:16:48,140
We'll start with Lin Zhanqiao,

315
00:16:49,260 --> 00:16:50,620
and poach the talented rookies

316
00:16:51,180 --> 00:16:52,740
her editors are managing.

317
00:16:53,220 --> 00:16:54,060
The rookies?

318
00:16:54,700 --> 00:16:55,580
I already told them

319
00:16:55,580 --> 00:16:56,660
we're changing our terms.

320
00:16:57,022 --> 00:16:58,377
No more monthly salaries.

321
00:16:58,660 --> 00:17:00,020
Bonuses based on click tiers.

322
00:17:00,740 --> 00:17:01,780
A lot of them

323
00:17:01,780 --> 00:17:02,820
will struggle to live.

324
00:17:03,220 --> 00:17:04,020
That just proves

325
00:17:04,020 --> 00:17:05,311
they aren't meant for this.

326
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:07,140
Why didn't you discuss this with me?

327
00:17:09,020 --> 00:17:10,140
If you land Gu Yan,

328
00:17:10,140 --> 00:17:11,700
would you even care

329
00:17:11,700 --> 00:17:12,780
how I deal with the rookies?

330
00:17:12,940 --> 00:17:14,300
You being so anxious now

331
00:17:14,300 --> 00:17:15,420
just proves that you can't

332
00:17:16,380 --> 00:17:16,820
land him.

333
00:17:17,900 --> 00:17:18,780
It's "us."

334
00:17:19,500 --> 00:17:20,780
This isn't just on me.

335
00:17:21,660 --> 00:17:22,500
Startups are hard.

336
00:17:22,711 --> 00:17:24,022
Survival of the fittest.

337
00:17:25,460 --> 00:17:26,820
If you can't deliver,

338
00:17:27,900 --> 00:17:30,380
I'll have to consider other partners.

339
00:17:39,940 --> 00:17:40,740
I'll walk you back.

340
00:17:41,460 --> 00:17:41,900
No need.

341
00:17:42,088 --> 00:17:43,300
I'm staying at my place today.

342
00:17:43,660 --> 00:17:44,580
It's across the street.

343
00:17:46,140 --> 00:17:46,900
I'll walk you over.

344
00:17:49,020 --> 00:17:49,340
Okay.

345
00:18:00,466 --> 00:18:01,866
I've always wanted to ask,

346
00:18:02,820 --> 00:18:05,020
why do you stay at Lin Zhanqiao's place

347
00:18:05,340 --> 00:18:06,540
instead of your own?

348
00:18:07,620 --> 00:18:09,700
Is her place closer to work?

349
00:18:11,140 --> 00:18:11,740
No.

350
00:18:12,980 --> 00:18:14,900
Traffic from her place is terrible.

351
00:18:16,400 --> 00:18:17,380
Then, are you afraid

352
00:18:18,260 --> 00:18:18,940
of being alone?

353
00:18:20,540 --> 00:18:21,060
Nope.

354
00:18:22,333 --> 00:18:24,244
You don't seem afraid of being alone.

355
00:18:27,180 --> 00:18:28,220
It's my mom's judgment.

356
00:18:29,140 --> 00:18:29,900
She's a neat freak.

357
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:32,260
Every time before she comes over,

358
00:18:32,540 --> 00:18:33,620
I have to clean up.

359
00:18:34,220 --> 00:18:35,580
But it never meets her standards.

360
00:18:37,300 --> 00:18:38,260
So then I figured,

361
00:18:38,844 --> 00:18:40,820
if someone lives there,
it'll never be spotless.

362
00:18:41,177 --> 00:18:42,380
So I just don't stay there.

363
00:18:42,940 --> 00:18:43,860
It's now a showroom.

364
00:18:58,420 --> 00:19:01,740
♪First time in love♪

365
00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:07,260
♪It tears my heart apart♪

366
00:19:09,580 --> 00:19:12,700
♪Keep chasing on♪

367
00:19:14,780 --> 00:19:18,220
♪Yet no one will ever know♪

368
00:19:20,500 --> 00:19:23,820
♪For long time♪

369
00:19:26,140 --> 00:19:29,820
♪Hope to lean on your side♪

370
00:19:31,380 --> 00:19:34,940
♪And here you are♪

371
00:19:37,140 --> 00:19:40,220
♪Calling my name in the air♪

372
00:19:42,460 --> 00:19:46,180
♪Stay with open arms♪

373
00:19:53,140 --> 00:19:55,140
(Bestseller List)

374
00:19:55,140 --> 00:19:57,020
(Amnesia: My Bossy,
Love-Obsessed Husband)

375
00:19:59,780 --> 00:20:01,820
Mimi's Love-Obsessed Husband

376
00:20:01,820 --> 00:20:04,100
hit number one on the women's chart.

377
00:20:04,460 --> 00:20:05,380
That's great news.

378
00:20:05,620 --> 00:20:06,900
We should celebrate.

379
00:20:07,220 --> 00:20:09,340
("Completely hooked and can't stop")

380
00:20:09,420 --> 00:20:11,500
(is popping up all over the comments.)

381
00:20:11,777 --> 00:20:13,820
(Dingqi Livestream)
(Based on the current data,)

382
00:20:14,100 --> 00:20:16,580
(Drunk Old Friend
is gaining serious momentum.)

383
00:20:16,580 --> 00:20:19,540
I've never seen you
care so much about a rookie.

384
00:20:21,700 --> 00:20:23,500
I'm verifying your theory.

385
00:20:23,940 --> 00:20:24,980
What theory?

386
00:20:26,540 --> 00:20:28,700
That Gu Yan
is Lin Zhanqiao's secret weapon.

387
00:20:38,300 --> 00:20:41,140
(Online Fan Meet: Drunk Old Friend)

388
00:20:41,140 --> 00:20:44,540
(Hit Author: Gu Yan)

389
00:20:45,540 --> 00:20:47,380
Today, we are honored to invite

390
00:20:47,380 --> 00:20:48,740
the author himself, Gu Yan,

391
00:20:48,900 --> 00:20:50,780
and his talent scout editor

392
00:20:50,900 --> 00:20:52,060
to our livestream

393
00:20:52,260 --> 00:20:53,100
to meet everyone.

394
00:20:56,100 --> 00:20:56,820
Let Mr. Fan know

395
00:20:57,140 --> 00:20:57,844
Gu Yan is here.

396
00:21:24,420 --> 00:21:25,100
Lin Zhanqiao?

397
00:21:32,940 --> 00:21:33,380
Gu Yan?

398
00:21:38,780 --> 00:21:39,420
My author.

399
00:21:45,260 --> 00:21:45,740
Mr. Fan.

400
00:21:46,060 --> 00:21:46,540
Zhanqiao.

401
00:21:47,100 --> 00:21:49,020
We can finally
announce our collaboration.

402
00:21:50,180 --> 00:21:50,820
Young man.

403
00:21:51,660 --> 00:21:53,100
Your new update yesterday

404
00:21:53,420 --> 00:21:54,940
set another click record.

405
00:21:56,088 --> 00:21:57,177
It's very promising.

406
00:21:57,466 --> 00:21:57,940
Let's go.

407
00:21:58,100 --> 00:21:58,300
Come.

408
00:21:58,300 --> 00:21:59,000
Have a seat inside.

409
00:22:04,020 --> 00:22:05,260
Alright, book lovers,

410
00:22:05,340 --> 00:22:07,060
you can see who has joined

411
00:22:07,140 --> 00:22:08,111
our livestream today.

412
00:22:08,155 --> 00:22:10,460
We have the author himself, Gu Yan,

413
00:22:10,740 --> 00:22:13,260
and our star editor, Ms. Zhanqiao.

414
00:22:13,340 --> 00:22:14,420
(Welcome to both of you.)

415
00:22:17,300 --> 00:22:18,980
(So, Gu Yan, could you briefly)

416
00:22:18,980 --> 00:22:20,380
(introduce your background?)

417
00:22:32,940 --> 00:22:34,660
Gu Yan, may I ask

418
00:22:34,820 --> 00:22:36,311
what Zhanqiao whispered to you?

419
00:22:37,140 --> 00:22:37,660
She...

420
00:22:38,020 --> 00:22:38,980
She just told me

421
00:22:39,580 --> 00:22:41,100
to tell the truth.

422
00:22:41,860 --> 00:22:42,740
It was pretty cool.

423
00:22:43,060 --> 00:22:43,820
(As we all know,)

424
00:22:43,820 --> 00:22:46,220
(talent is common,
but a good scout is rare.)

425
00:22:46,700 --> 00:22:48,410
(Ms. Lin has a sharp eye)

426
00:22:48,410 --> 00:22:50,140
(and exceptional abilities.)

427
00:22:55,660 --> 00:22:56,980
You've grown, Lin Zhanqiao.

428
00:23:01,540 --> 00:23:02,340
Are you jealous?

429
00:23:03,100 --> 00:23:03,940
Why would I be?

430
00:23:04,540 --> 00:23:05,820
I'm happy for her.

431
00:23:05,820 --> 00:23:07,380
She finally found a good card to play.

432
00:23:09,060 --> 00:23:10,300
Lin Zhanqiao has been holding

433
00:23:10,300 --> 00:23:11,420
this card for a long time.

434
00:23:11,540 --> 00:23:12,620
At least

435
00:23:13,220 --> 00:23:14,060
half a year.

436
00:23:17,688 --> 00:23:18,820
Why are you looking at me?

437
00:23:20,660 --> 00:23:21,500
Now it seems

438
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:22,820
this card is being used against

439
00:23:22,820 --> 00:23:24,500
Zhao Lanxin and Ling Yikai.

440
00:23:24,700 --> 00:23:26,180
But initially, it must have been

441
00:23:26,380 --> 00:23:27,620
to replace you.

442
00:23:28,100 --> 00:23:28,700
No surprise.

443
00:23:29,380 --> 00:23:30,500
I'm not exactly

444
00:23:30,500 --> 00:23:31,700
a cooperative author.

445
00:23:31,700 --> 00:23:33,220
She's wanted to replace me for a while.

446
00:23:33,540 --> 00:23:34,050
Of course,

447
00:23:34,050 --> 00:23:35,740
Gu Yan could never replace me.

448
00:23:36,820 --> 00:23:37,810
And Lin Zhanqiao

449
00:23:37,810 --> 00:23:39,200
doesn't have any confidence in him.

450
00:23:39,300 --> 00:23:40,800
Or she would've released this sooner.

451
00:23:41,260 --> 00:23:42,620
When Zhao Lanxin challenged her,

452
00:23:42,620 --> 00:23:43,940
she forced him into the spotlight.

453
00:23:52,340 --> 00:23:53,500
When did you find Gu Yan?

454
00:23:54,620 --> 00:23:55,500
It's been a while.

455
00:23:55,940 --> 00:23:57,300
I've never seen a contract for him.

456
00:23:57,666 --> 00:23:58,980
I haven't signed the contract yet.

457
00:24:00,260 --> 00:24:00,660
Why not?

458
00:24:01,044 --> 00:24:02,088
Guarding against us?

459
00:24:02,580 --> 00:24:03,540
You couldn't have known

460
00:24:03,540 --> 00:24:04,933
Ling Yikai and I were leaving.

461
00:24:05,060 --> 00:24:06,340
I'm not that clairvoyant.

462
00:24:08,420 --> 00:24:09,460
But after so long,

463
00:24:10,140 --> 00:24:11,260
I know the kind of person

464
00:24:11,260 --> 00:24:12,100
Ling Yikai is.

465
00:24:12,700 --> 00:24:13,380
He worked so hard

466
00:24:13,380 --> 00:24:14,780
to secure the Zhiyuan Investment,

467
00:24:15,500 --> 00:24:17,180
and kept me completely out of the loop.

468
00:24:18,220 --> 00:24:19,060
I had a feeling

469
00:24:19,060 --> 00:24:20,020
he'd negotiate with me.

470
00:24:24,980 --> 00:24:26,140
I was guarding against him.

471
00:24:26,980 --> 00:24:27,500
I didn't know

472
00:24:28,060 --> 00:24:28,740
you'd leave.

473
00:24:30,020 --> 00:24:30,780
Keeping it from me

474
00:24:30,780 --> 00:24:31,980
is guarding against me.

475
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:34,900
Do you really think
Gu Yan can surpass He Han?

476
00:24:35,220 --> 00:24:35,900
It's up to him.

477
00:24:37,100 --> 00:24:38,620
At least he's surpassed Hong Qigong.

478
00:24:57,577 --> 00:24:59,020
Did you watch Gu Yan's livestream?

479
00:25:00,020 --> 00:25:01,140
Congratulations, Ms. Lin.

480
00:25:01,140 --> 00:25:02,740
Nice trick, keeping him hidden.

481
00:25:02,740 --> 00:25:04,044
But I'm a bit busy right now.

482
00:25:04,060 --> 00:25:04,900
I'm just heading out

483
00:25:04,900 --> 00:25:06,660
to celebrate Mimi hitting number one.

484
00:25:12,340 --> 00:25:14,060
(Honestly, Drunk Old Friend)

485
00:25:14,660 --> 00:25:16,060
(wouldn't be where it is today)

486
00:25:16,500 --> 00:25:18,660
(without my editor,)

487
00:25:18,980 --> 00:25:20,980
(also my boss, Ms. Lin.)

488
00:25:21,460 --> 00:25:22,620
Before I met her,

489
00:25:23,780 --> 00:25:25,940
I opened an internet cafe with a friend.

490
00:25:26,888 --> 00:25:28,580
I worked the night shift every night.

491
00:25:29,540 --> 00:25:30,540
When it got busy,

492
00:25:30,622 --> 00:25:32,760
(Mengtong Internet Cafe, Year 2023)
the new computers were taken.

493
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:35,020
I could only
use the old ones to read web novels.

494
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:37,140
After reading so many,

495
00:25:37,740 --> 00:25:38,820
I started writing my own.

496
00:25:40,340 --> 00:25:41,580
Ms. Lin discovered me.

497
00:25:43,020 --> 00:25:45,020
There was a line I wrote
in Drunk Old Friend.

498
00:25:45,700 --> 00:25:47,340
"Drunk, I miss the vast misty waters.

499
00:25:48,220 --> 00:25:50,060
Waking, my old friend's tea is still warm."

500
00:25:51,220 --> 00:25:53,220
This inscription in Drunk Old Friend

501
00:25:53,220 --> 00:25:54,555
was written for Lin Zhanqiao.

502
00:25:55,180 --> 00:25:56,380
I could even say

503
00:25:56,740 --> 00:25:58,540
that the entirety of Drunk Old Friend

504
00:25:58,780 --> 00:26:00,060
was written for Lin Zhanqiao.

505
00:26:00,620 --> 00:26:03,140
Just like how books always had

506
00:26:03,444 --> 00:26:05,380
"Dedicated to so-and-so"
on the title page.

507
00:26:05,466 --> 00:26:06,400
It's the same idea.

508
00:26:07,100 --> 00:26:08,540
Before I met Lin Zhanqiao,

509
00:26:08,577 --> 00:26:10,666
I was just
a night-shift internet cafe admin.

510
00:26:11,220 --> 00:26:12,140
In a basement,

511
00:26:12,620 --> 00:26:15,540
wearing headphones, smoking, swearing,
and eating instant noodles.

512
00:26:16,340 --> 00:26:18,180
Writing novels was just an outlet.

513
00:26:19,220 --> 00:26:21,420
Like daydreaming.

514
00:26:21,888 --> 00:26:23,688
(Annihilation Secret)
Dreaming of getting rich.

515
00:26:23,733 --> 00:26:25,311
(The Return of the Phantom Knight)
Dreaming of moving up.

516
00:26:25,460 --> 00:26:26,666
Dreaming of being a hero.

517
00:26:27,660 --> 00:26:29,300
I wouldn't even call them dreams.

518
00:26:29,940 --> 00:26:30,580
At best,

519
00:26:31,340 --> 00:26:32,460
they were delusions.

520
00:26:33,460 --> 00:26:34,940
Until Lin Zhanqiao found me.

521
00:26:36,380 --> 00:26:37,460
When I saw her,

522
00:26:38,380 --> 00:26:39,180
I felt like

523
00:26:39,940 --> 00:26:41,420
I had known her for a long time.

524
00:26:42,020 --> 00:26:42,700
Or rather,

525
00:26:43,666 --> 00:26:44,180
I felt like

526
00:26:44,180 --> 00:26:46,140
I was meant to wait here
for someone like her.

527
00:26:47,260 --> 00:26:48,220
To pick

528
00:26:48,888 --> 00:26:50,977
a piece of trash like me
out of the dumpster.

529
00:26:52,260 --> 00:26:53,740
To give me validation and support

530
00:26:53,820 --> 00:26:54,620
without disgust.

531
00:26:55,940 --> 00:26:56,820
In my whole life,

532
00:26:57,580 --> 00:26:58,300
no one has ever

533
00:26:58,300 --> 00:27:00,060
given me so much patience and time.

534
00:27:01,140 --> 00:27:02,820
If you like the story

535
00:27:03,460 --> 00:27:04,500
you are reading now,

536
00:27:05,500 --> 00:27:06,860
it's not because of Gu Yan.

537
00:27:07,800 --> 00:27:09,060
It's because of Lin Zhanqiao.

538
00:27:10,020 --> 00:27:11,540
All the praise and honors I receive

539
00:27:12,180 --> 00:27:13,140
in my past, present,

540
00:27:13,740 --> 00:27:15,740
and future,

541
00:27:16,740 --> 00:27:18,900
should first belong to Lin Zhanqiao.

542
00:27:20,100 --> 00:27:20,980
She taught me,

543
00:27:21,444 --> 00:27:22,380
and encouraged me.

544
00:27:23,340 --> 00:27:25,340
That's the only reason
you are able to read

545
00:27:26,300 --> 00:27:27,420
these chapters today.

546
00:27:37,660 --> 00:27:38,700
This place is nice.

547
00:27:38,780 --> 00:27:39,500
Of course.

548
00:27:39,740 --> 00:27:40,940
It's quite lively here.

549
00:27:41,660 --> 00:27:42,466
Let's sit there.

550
00:27:42,660 --> 00:27:42,980
Okay.

551
00:27:43,900 --> 00:27:44,700
Hello, Mr. He.

552
00:27:44,700 --> 00:27:45,340
I'm Zhangzhu,

553
00:27:45,540 --> 00:27:46,780
Ms. Lin's assistant at Chenxing.

554
00:27:47,180 --> 00:27:48,260
We met yesterday, right?

555
00:27:48,260 --> 00:27:48,900
Remember me?

556
00:27:48,900 --> 00:27:49,860
The number one fan.

557
00:27:49,860 --> 00:27:51,100
Yes, your fan.

558
00:27:51,620 --> 00:27:52,500
Hello, I'm Mimi.

559
00:27:53,180 --> 00:27:54,660
I'm He Han's girlfriend.

560
00:27:55,540 --> 00:27:57,140
Meeting a Love-Obsessed Husband.

561
00:27:57,266 --> 00:27:59,020
Congratulations
on hitting number one today.

562
00:27:59,300 --> 00:27:59,860
Thank you.

563
00:27:59,955 --> 00:28:00,620
You're welcome.

564
00:28:00,620 --> 00:28:01,400
Where's your boss?

565
00:28:01,740 --> 00:28:02,980
Livestreaming with Gu Yan.

566
00:28:02,980 --> 00:28:03,620
They'll be here.

567
00:28:03,900 --> 00:28:05,060
I came ahead to order.

568
00:28:05,380 --> 00:28:06,380
What a coincidence.

569
00:28:07,060 --> 00:28:08,340
Let's sit together, then.

570
00:28:09,933 --> 00:28:10,600
Together...

571
00:28:11,180 --> 00:28:11,940
Sit here?

572
00:28:12,380 --> 00:28:12,780
This...

573
00:28:12,940 --> 00:28:14,300
Is it inconvenient?

574
00:28:15,860 --> 00:28:16,340
This...

575
00:28:17,100 --> 00:28:18,000
What a coincidence.

576
00:28:21,340 --> 00:28:21,780
Ms. Lin.

577
00:28:22,220 --> 00:28:23,220
Mr. He is here

578
00:28:23,220 --> 00:28:25,100
to celebrate
his girlfriend's top ranking.

579
00:28:25,860 --> 00:28:26,780
Let me introduce you.

580
00:28:27,340 --> 00:28:27,780
Gu Yan.

581
00:28:28,660 --> 00:28:29,020
He Han.

582
00:28:29,860 --> 00:28:30,340
Zhangzhu.

583
00:28:30,940 --> 00:28:31,340
Mimi.

584
00:28:33,820 --> 00:28:34,700
Hello, Mr. He.

585
00:28:36,300 --> 00:28:37,140
Don't call me Mr. He.

586
00:28:37,300 --> 00:28:37,980
Call me senior.

587
00:28:38,420 --> 00:28:39,740
After all, our mutual mentor

588
00:28:39,740 --> 00:28:40,900
is Ms. Lin Zhanqiao.

589
00:28:41,380 --> 00:28:42,300
And let me tell you,

590
00:28:42,620 --> 00:28:44,020
I gave you this month

591
00:28:44,020 --> 00:28:45,860
so you could seize the opportunity

592
00:28:45,980 --> 00:28:46,940
to have a head start.

593
00:28:47,740 --> 00:28:50,044
Because Ms. Lin has been
having a run of bad luck lately.

594
00:28:50,100 --> 00:28:51,920
She can only rely on you
to boost her career.

595
00:28:52,380 --> 00:28:53,220
I'll do my best.

596
00:28:53,820 --> 00:28:55,420
But you're the ceiling in this industry.

597
00:28:55,820 --> 00:28:56,820
I'll learn from you.

598
00:28:57,420 --> 00:28:58,620
Don't stress yourself out.

599
00:28:59,500 --> 00:29:01,020
After all, I met He Han when he was

600
00:29:01,220 --> 00:29:02,220
in his early twenties.

601
00:29:02,700 --> 00:29:04,260
He wasn't even as good as you now.

602
00:29:05,420 --> 00:29:05,980
Of course.

603
00:29:06,940 --> 00:29:08,820
I was only twenty myself back then.

604
00:29:09,580 --> 00:29:10,460
As an editor,

605
00:29:10,660 --> 00:29:12,300
my experience
wasn't what it is now.

606
00:29:12,900 --> 00:29:13,900
Completely incompetent.

607
00:29:17,740 --> 00:29:20,140
Ms. Lin, should we
move to another table?

608
00:29:20,340 --> 00:29:22,180
Because it seems
He Han wants to sit here.

609
00:29:22,620 --> 00:29:23,660
I'm afraid it might be

610
00:29:23,660 --> 00:29:25,300
inconvenient when we talk business.

611
00:29:25,300 --> 00:29:26,100
No need.

612
00:29:26,180 --> 00:29:27,700
We'll leave. You guys chat here.

613
00:29:28,180 --> 00:29:29,700
Come, sit down.

614
00:29:30,020 --> 00:29:30,300
Sit.

615
00:29:31,540 --> 00:29:31,980
Enjoy.

616
00:29:33,740 --> 00:29:35,650
Excuse me. Please bring out our cake.

617
00:29:35,650 --> 00:29:36,180
Thank you.

618
00:29:44,140 --> 00:29:45,260
I need to record this.

619
00:29:47,740 --> 00:29:49,060
I want to film the finger heart.

620
00:29:49,180 --> 00:29:49,980
Yeah, like so.

621
00:29:50,540 --> 00:29:51,777
Put it together with mine.

622
00:29:58,700 --> 00:29:59,620
Yay!

623
00:30:00,100 --> 00:30:01,460
I, Mimi, have reached the top!

624
00:30:03,460 --> 00:30:04,380
The top!

625
00:30:05,940 --> 00:30:06,740
I want to eat that.

626
00:30:06,740 --> 00:30:07,900
Want to join them, Zhangzhu?

627
00:30:10,340 --> 00:30:10,700
No.

628
00:30:11,660 --> 00:30:13,940
I just didn't expect He Han to be so...

629
00:30:14,780 --> 00:30:15,340
Cheesy?

630
00:30:16,700 --> 00:30:18,820
No, just different from what I imagined.

631
00:30:22,780 --> 00:30:24,620
I didn't expect you to be so young.

632
00:30:24,620 --> 00:30:25,377
How old are you?

633
00:30:25,860 --> 00:30:26,380
Twenty-six.

634
00:30:27,460 --> 00:30:28,311
I'm twenty-two.

635
00:30:29,020 --> 00:30:29,380
Okay.

636
00:30:31,860 --> 00:30:33,580
You don't seem to talk much.

637
00:30:34,300 --> 00:30:35,340
Why do your characters

638
00:30:35,340 --> 00:30:36,260
talk so much?

639
00:30:37,380 --> 00:30:38,540
Isn't it true that authors

640
00:30:39,660 --> 00:30:40,620
give their protagonists

641
00:30:40,860 --> 00:30:42,220
whatever they lack themselves?

642
00:30:43,260 --> 00:30:44,060
Wish fulfillment.

643
00:30:45,660 --> 00:30:46,540
Lean back.

644
00:30:47,060 --> 00:30:47,500
Lean back.

645
00:30:48,711 --> 00:30:49,733
I'll lean back too.

646
00:30:49,860 --> 00:30:50,600
I'll do it too.

647
00:30:51,380 --> 00:30:52,660
So, do you read He Han's novels?

648
00:30:53,900 --> 00:30:54,220
I have.

649
00:30:54,220 --> 00:30:55,111
What do you think?

650
00:30:56,700 --> 00:30:57,420
I feel like

651
00:30:58,700 --> 00:30:59,800
I'm the better writer.

652
00:31:00,340 --> 00:31:01,220
In a month,

653
00:31:01,700 --> 00:31:02,620
I might surpass him.

654
00:31:04,740 --> 00:31:05,688
I admire your spirit.

655
00:31:06,060 --> 00:31:06,900
No one has ever dared

656
00:31:06,900 --> 00:31:08,180
to challenge He Han before.

657
00:31:08,777 --> 00:31:09,300
Good luck.

658
00:31:14,700 --> 00:31:15,220
What?

659
00:31:16,100 --> 00:31:17,140
You went into my bedroom?

660
00:31:22,860 --> 00:31:24,380
I didn't go in there on purpose.

661
00:31:24,380 --> 00:31:25,580
I just couldn't find my stuff,

662
00:31:25,580 --> 00:31:26,940
so I went in to look.

663
00:31:26,940 --> 00:31:28,060
That's still not okay.

664
00:31:29,140 --> 00:31:30,780
But there's no one else in your room,

665
00:31:30,780 --> 00:31:32,060
and you have nothing to hide.

666
00:31:32,220 --> 00:31:33,420
Why do you care so much?

667
00:31:33,900 --> 00:31:35,740
It's not about what's in my bedroom.

668
00:31:35,740 --> 00:31:37,540
It's about you breaking our agreement.

669
00:31:43,660 --> 00:31:44,740
Fine, I was wrong.

670
00:31:45,140 --> 00:31:46,540
I won't do it again, okay?

671
00:31:46,780 --> 00:31:47,660
There is no "again."

672
00:31:48,860 --> 00:31:49,980
Do you not love me anymore?

673
00:31:50,140 --> 00:31:50,540
I don't.

674
00:31:53,380 --> 00:31:54,740
You said you loved me.

675
00:31:54,740 --> 00:31:56,620
That you'd make me
incredibly successful.

676
00:31:57,060 --> 00:31:58,140
You've reached the top.

677
00:31:58,140 --> 00:31:59,140
Isn't that enough?

678
00:31:59,980 --> 00:32:00,740
But you said

679
00:32:01,460 --> 00:32:02,700
you loved me the most.

680
00:32:02,700 --> 00:32:04,060
And that you were going to marry me.

681
00:32:04,060 --> 00:32:05,020
You said you'd accept

682
00:32:05,020 --> 00:32:06,210
all my flaws.

683
00:32:06,210 --> 00:32:07,100
I absolutely did not.

684
00:32:07,222 --> 00:32:09,020
That's what the male lead
in your novel said.

685
00:32:09,140 --> 00:32:09,700
Not me.

686
00:32:09,700 --> 00:32:11,140
The male lead is you!

687
00:32:11,140 --> 00:32:12,220
And I'm the female lead!

688
00:32:12,220 --> 00:32:13,540
You decided that on your own.

689
00:32:17,900 --> 00:32:18,700
What do you mean?

690
00:32:21,460 --> 00:32:22,060
I think

691
00:32:24,380 --> 00:32:25,260
we should break up.

692
00:32:32,380 --> 00:32:33,220
He Han...

693
00:32:36,380 --> 00:32:36,940
He Han!

694
00:32:36,940 --> 00:32:38,780
Why would you dump me

695
00:32:38,780 --> 00:32:40,100
right at my peak?

696
00:32:40,260 --> 00:32:42,500
Wouldn't it be worse
to dump you at your lowest?

697
00:33:00,300 --> 00:33:01,860
Oh my god. That's so humiliating.

698
00:33:04,620 --> 00:33:05,740
Don't worry. He's fine.

699
00:33:06,533 --> 00:33:07,444
He's used to it.

700
00:33:07,820 --> 00:33:08,900
You think that's fine?

701
00:33:09,340 --> 00:33:11,260
It might bother someone else, but

702
00:33:11,980 --> 00:33:13,460
he's probably enjoying it.

703
00:33:29,260 --> 00:33:30,500
Looks like my luck is bad too.

704
00:33:32,060 --> 00:33:32,740
Sorry about that.

705
00:33:33,020 --> 00:33:33,860
Did I scare you?

706
00:33:34,860 --> 00:33:36,180
We're having a work meeting here.

707
00:33:36,500 --> 00:33:37,340
It's not a good time.

708
00:33:37,420 --> 00:33:38,580
That's okay. I don't mind.

709
00:33:43,220 --> 00:33:44,940
What was my junior's pen name again?

710
00:33:45,380 --> 00:33:46,540
Return of the Phantom Knight?

711
00:33:47,333 --> 00:33:49,300
The Phantom Knight
stopped writing ages ago.

712
00:33:49,300 --> 00:33:50,220
How did he return?

713
00:33:51,222 --> 00:33:52,400
Just paying tribute.

714
00:33:52,940 --> 00:33:54,340
Even though his writing

715
00:33:54,622 --> 00:33:56,340
falls far short compared to the original

716
00:33:56,340 --> 00:33:57,260
Phantom Knight,

717
00:33:57,820 --> 00:33:58,980
it still has its moments.

718
00:33:59,700 --> 00:34:01,140
I've heard of the Phantom Knight.

719
00:34:01,311 --> 00:34:02,300
He can be considered

720
00:34:02,300 --> 00:34:04,100
the founding father of online fiction.

721
00:34:04,420 --> 00:34:05,060
But later on,

722
00:34:05,300 --> 00:34:06,460
he suddenly stopped writing.

723
00:34:07,140 --> 00:34:07,780
Back then,

724
00:34:07,780 --> 00:34:09,300
online authors didn't use real names.

725
00:34:09,700 --> 00:34:12,380
So no one knows who he really is.

726
00:34:12,940 --> 00:34:13,860
I just figured

727
00:34:14,460 --> 00:34:15,580
that borrowing his name

728
00:34:15,660 --> 00:34:17,060
wouldn't cause any trouble.

729
00:34:17,780 --> 00:34:18,780
Mr. He, Ms. Lin.

730
00:34:19,244 --> 00:34:20,060
You're experienced.

731
00:34:20,060 --> 00:34:21,370
Have you ever met Phantom Knight?

732
00:34:21,370 --> 00:34:22,177
- No.
- No.

733
00:34:23,020 --> 00:34:23,940
If he came back,

734
00:34:23,940 --> 00:34:25,100
all of us could stop writing.

735
00:34:25,380 --> 00:34:26,340
Seriously.

736
00:34:26,340 --> 00:34:27,220
We'd be sent packing.

737
00:34:28,260 --> 00:34:29,740
That was over a decade ago.

738
00:34:30,140 --> 00:34:31,133
If he really came back,

739
00:34:31,740 --> 00:34:32,540
I could still win.

740
00:34:33,200 --> 00:34:35,688
Just focus on getting over
the hill in front of you first.

741
00:34:38,740 --> 00:34:39,180
Alright.

742
00:34:39,540 --> 00:34:40,380
Take your time.

743
00:34:40,700 --> 00:34:41,380
I'm taking off.

744
00:34:45,940 --> 00:34:46,980
Only twenty days left

745
00:34:47,100 --> 00:34:47,940
until the deadline.

746
00:34:48,740 --> 00:34:49,700
Keep at it, Junior.

747
00:34:49,700 --> 00:34:50,620
Make our mentor proud.

748
00:35:01,060 --> 00:35:01,500
Well?

749
00:35:01,733 --> 00:35:02,820
Did the idol's true color

750
00:35:03,260 --> 00:35:03,740
hurt you?

751
00:35:05,060 --> 00:35:06,660
Don't you think he's super cute?

752
00:35:16,740 --> 00:35:18,340
(Hello, everyone, I'm Mimi!)

753
00:35:18,700 --> 00:35:20,900
(Today is a day of double blessings.)

754
00:35:20,933 --> 00:35:21,730
(The first is that)

755
00:35:21,730 --> 00:35:23,620
(Fans lining up)
("Love-Obsessed Husband" has reached)

756
00:35:23,620 --> 00:35:25,888
(Number one fan is here)
(the top of the women's chart!)

757
00:35:26,060 --> 00:35:27,580
(Thank you all for your love.)

758
00:35:27,860 --> 00:35:29,940
(And thank you
for your ongoing support.)

759
00:35:30,140 --> 00:35:31,420
(I will continue to write)

760
00:35:31,420 --> 00:35:32,620
(many more great stories.)

761
00:35:32,780 --> 00:35:34,300
(Please look forward to them.)

762
00:35:34,333 --> 00:35:34,980
(I love you guys!)

763
00:35:37,200 --> 00:35:38,600
(Who is this?)
(The second is that)

764
00:35:38,660 --> 00:35:40,980
(A new work?)
(I finally saw him for who he truly is)

765
00:35:41,022 --> 00:35:42,466
(What are we talking about?)
(and I dumped him!)

766
00:35:45,580 --> 00:35:47,620
Do you think it's worth it for He Han?

767
00:35:47,822 --> 00:35:48,740
He helped her succeed

768
00:35:48,740 --> 00:35:50,180
only to get publicly trashed.

769
00:35:50,940 --> 00:35:51,940
Mimi leaves,

770
00:35:51,940 --> 00:35:54,022
and another Lily
or Niuniu will take her place.

771
00:35:54,780 --> 00:35:55,620
They know the deal.

772
00:35:55,700 --> 00:35:56,780
As long as they date him,

773
00:35:56,860 --> 00:35:58,420
their novels will shoot up the charts.

774
00:35:58,780 --> 00:35:59,660
Plenty are willing.

775
00:36:00,180 --> 00:36:01,260
But honestly,

776
00:36:02,260 --> 00:36:03,140
if he dates

777
00:36:03,140 --> 00:36:04,380
only one girlfriend for a while,

778
00:36:04,380 --> 00:36:06,140
breaks up, and then dates the next,

779
00:36:06,380 --> 00:36:07,340
it's fine.

780
00:36:08,140 --> 00:36:09,100
And he genuinely

781
00:36:09,100 --> 00:36:10,660
helps each girlfriend get on the charts.

782
00:36:11,220 --> 00:36:12,660
In a sense,

783
00:36:13,260 --> 00:36:15,060
that makes him a high-quality boyfriend.

784
00:36:26,580 --> 00:36:27,740
He met Gu Yan today.

785
00:36:30,380 --> 00:36:31,140
Was it tense?

786
00:36:31,860 --> 00:36:32,820
He's jealous of Gu Yan.

787
00:36:33,580 --> 00:36:34,340
I could tell.

788
00:36:35,620 --> 00:36:36,260
Tell the truth,

789
00:36:36,555 --> 00:36:38,111
is Gu Yan your little boyfriend?

790
00:36:38,220 --> 00:36:38,700
No.

791
00:36:39,333 --> 00:36:41,180
It's just an author-editor relationship.

792
00:36:41,460 --> 00:36:42,980
An author and editor

793
00:36:42,980 --> 00:36:44,500
can be boyfriend and girlfriend too.

794
00:36:44,977 --> 00:36:46,222
It's better not to be.

795
00:36:47,100 --> 00:36:48,340
Do you regret breaking up

796
00:36:48,420 --> 00:36:49,180
with He Han?

797
00:36:49,540 --> 00:36:50,340
Regret what?

798
00:36:51,244 --> 00:36:52,260
If we hadn't broken up,

799
00:36:52,533 --> 00:36:53,660
Gu Yan wouldn't have been

800
00:36:53,660 --> 00:36:55,020
forced into the spotlight,

801
00:36:55,511 --> 00:36:57,260
and wouldn't be
an overnight success now.

802
00:36:57,500 --> 00:36:58,860
I didn't mean professionally.

803
00:36:59,220 --> 00:37:00,311
You mean his character?

804
00:37:02,540 --> 00:37:03,460
Just two words.

805
00:37:04,380 --> 00:37:04,900
Selfish.

806
00:37:05,700 --> 00:37:06,377
Narcissistic.

807
00:37:08,340 --> 00:37:09,420
He Han still loves you.

808
00:37:11,660 --> 00:37:13,060
At least, I think he still does.

809
00:37:29,060 --> 00:37:29,700
He said

810
00:37:30,460 --> 00:37:31,340
he loves me.

811
00:37:33,140 --> 00:37:34,060
But everyone

812
00:37:35,220 --> 00:37:36,580
expresses love differently.

813
00:37:40,100 --> 00:37:41,140
He says he loves me.

814
00:37:42,340 --> 00:37:43,980
But he can't share his life with me

815
00:37:44,580 --> 00:37:45,940
long-term and stably.

816
00:37:52,700 --> 00:37:53,740
He writes so many novels,

817
00:37:55,300 --> 00:37:56,740
and he really thinks he's trapped in

818
00:37:56,940 --> 00:37:58,690
some tragic past life memory

819
00:37:58,690 --> 00:37:59,711
that he can't reveal.

820
00:38:00,300 --> 00:38:02,180
That he has to stay away
from the mortal world

821
00:38:03,220 --> 00:38:04,140
and worldly love.

822
00:38:04,500 --> 00:38:05,340
Otherwise,

823
00:38:05,420 --> 00:38:07,240
he'll drag
everyone around him down to ashes,

824
00:38:07,340 --> 00:38:09,140
or even send them
to eternal damnation.

825
00:38:11,100 --> 00:38:12,020
But stories like that

826
00:38:12,020 --> 00:38:13,540
only fool young girls.

827
00:38:14,140 --> 00:38:16,180
I have produced
hundreds of stories like that.

828
00:38:17,540 --> 00:38:18,460
I don't buy it.

829
00:38:24,466 --> 00:38:25,860
Please give this to Lawyer Bei.

830
00:38:26,400 --> 00:38:27,900
It's Chenxing's contract with Gu Yan.

831
00:38:28,500 --> 00:38:29,900
I want the terms to be more binding.

832
00:38:30,740 --> 00:38:31,260
Why?

833
00:38:31,740 --> 00:38:32,580
Don't you trust him?

834
00:38:33,420 --> 00:38:35,220
He seems like an honest young man.

835
00:38:35,300 --> 00:38:37,180
That's because
he hasn't met enough people,

836
00:38:37,260 --> 00:38:38,580
and temptations yet.

837
00:38:39,860 --> 00:38:40,500
But, you know,

838
00:38:42,900 --> 00:38:43,820
people change.

839
00:38:46,940 --> 00:38:48,180
(Questionnaire)

840
00:38:48,180 --> 00:38:48,820
Are you done?

841
00:38:51,022 --> 00:38:52,666
There are hundreds of questions.

842
00:38:53,620 --> 00:38:55,380
And you paid a thousand yuan for them?

843
00:38:56,300 --> 00:38:57,180
I could have

844
00:38:57,460 --> 00:38:58,260
taken you to a bar

845
00:38:58,260 --> 00:38:59,266
for five hundred yuan.

846
00:39:00,740 --> 00:39:02,380
This does precision matching.

847
00:39:02,980 --> 00:39:04,260
The guys you meet at bars

848
00:39:04,660 --> 00:39:05,980
are just lonely and looking for

849
00:39:05,980 --> 00:39:06,940
a good time.

850
00:39:08,860 --> 00:39:10,060
So you spend a thousand,

851
00:39:10,420 --> 00:39:11,220
and that guarantees

852
00:39:11,220 --> 00:39:12,580
they want a serious relationship?

853
00:39:12,980 --> 00:39:14,300
He Han spent more on you.

854
00:39:15,940 --> 00:39:16,711
It's different.

855
00:39:17,540 --> 00:39:19,180
This ensures our values align.

856
00:39:22,140 --> 00:39:23,060
Look at this question.

857
00:39:24,180 --> 00:39:25,355
